{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_1","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"pwd && git status --short && sed -n '1,220p' __issue_context__.json\"","aggregated_output":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go\n D .github/copilot-instructions.md\n?? .agents/\n?? .claude/skills/skills\n?? AGENTS.md\n?? __agent_config__/\n?? __agent_prompt__.md\n?? __issue_context__.json\n?? __pr_result__/\n?? obo-scripts/\n{\n  \"body\": \"Please provide as much information as you can: \\n\\n* **GO term ID label:**\\nGO:0046544 development of secondary male sexual characteristics\\n\\n\\n* * **never in taxon: **\\n4751 fungi\\n\\n* **Supporting evidence if available (e.g PMID):**\\n\\nI think this can be updated from never in pombe/cerevisiae to never in fungi. I think it would be surprising to see a fungal protein annotated to secondary sex characteristic?\\n\",\n  \"comments\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7Ro1vK\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"Antonialock\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"actually, it's not propagated to fungi at the moment. I just saw the taxon constraint and thought it could be broadened.\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-11-11T14:20:24Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31051#issuecomment-3517144010\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7RpCW_\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"pgaudet\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"Only in Metazoa? \",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-11-11T14:32:02Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31051#issuecomment-3517195711\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7RpUmn\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"Antonialock\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"It looks like it might be valid for plants?\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-11-11T14:47:48Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31051#issuecomment-3517270439\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7R3eur\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"pgaudet\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"I think plants have sexual characteristics (or sex-differentiation), but not secondary? \\n\\nhttps://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/veterinary-science-and-veterinary-medicine/secondary-sex-characteristic#:~:text=Secondary%20sex%20characteristics%20refer%20to,in%20body%20composition%20and%20structure.\\n\\n@tberardini what do you think ? \\n\\nWhatever we decide, the TC should be removed from ' GO:0046544 development of secondary male sexual characteristics' and be added to the parent instead: **GO:0045136 development of secondary sexual characteristics**\\n\\n\\nThanks, Pascale\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-11-12T09:34:52Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31051#issuecomment-3520981931\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7R9mGO\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"Antonialock\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"So this is from wikipedia:\\n\\nMost [flowering plants](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flowering_plant) are [hermaphroditic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hermaphroditic) but approximately 6% of species have separate males and females ([dioecy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dioecy)).[[21]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexual_dimorphism#cite_note-Renner-1995-21) Sexual dimorphism is common in dioecious plants[[22]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexual_dimorphism#cite_note-22): 403  and [dioicous](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dioicy) species.[[23]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexual_dimorphism#cite_note-Ramawat-2016-23): 71\\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexual_dimorphism\\n\\nI don't know if \\\"secondary sex characteristics\\\" in plants is obscure and not a consensus belief, but there are references to it in the literature:\\n\\\"Gender-related differences in growth and concentration of secondary metabolites have been documented in dioecious plants. Males usually grow faster than females, whilst females allocate more resources to reproduction and chemical defences than males, hence their growth is reduced\\\" (2006 paper https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1146609X05000937)\\n(chemical defences and leaf size would be secondary characteristics?)\\n\\n\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-11-12T15:38:51Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": true,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31051#issuecomment-3522584974\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7R_o4Z\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"tberardini\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"\\nFound this paper; [**Secondary sex characters in plants**](https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02860717)\\n\\nNo TC on the 'development of secondary sexual characteristics' please. The current GO definition (below) refers to 'sex hormone secretion' which could be modified to 'hormone secretion' to be more general as plant hormones like ethylene and auxin affect secondary sex characters (see [**Hormonal Regulation of Sex Expression in Plants**](https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/chapter/bookseries/pii/S0083672905720033))\\n\\n>  \\tThe process whose specific outcome is the progression of the secondary sexual characteristics over time, from their formation to the mature structures. In humans, these include growth of axillary, chest, and pubic hair, voice changes, testicular/penile enlargement, breast development and menstrual periods. Development occurs in response to sex hormone secretion.\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-11-12T17:39:49Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31051#issuecomment-3523120665\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7STHOw\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"pgaudet\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"Thanks @tberardini \\n\\nIt seems we should somehow split these terms, as underlying mechanisms should be unrelated in plants and animals. \\n\\nBut for now we can remove the TC on GO:0046544 development of secondary male sexual characteristics and add 'never in fungi' for development of secondary sexual characteristics'.\\n\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-11-13T15:04:27Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31051#issuecomment-3528225712\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7St3sS\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"raymond91125\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"The TC on GO:0046544 development of secondary male sexual characteristics comes from inference thus is not easily removable. I added some missing relationships to GO:0045136 development of secondary sexual characteristics so that it now also has the same TC as GO:0046544. The specificity of TC comes from GO:0032501 multicellular organismal process. Specified in never_in_taxon.tsv\\nGO:0032501      multicellular organismal process        NCBITaxon:4896  Schizosaccharomyces pombe            \\nGO:0032501      multicellular organismal process        NCBITaxon:4932  Saccharomyces cerevisiae             \\nGO:0032501      multicellular organismal process        NCBITaxon:2     Bacteria        \\nGO:0032501      multicellular organismal process        NCBITaxon:2157  Archaea \\n\\nDo we want make GO:0032501 multicellular organismal process never_in_taxon Fungi?\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-11-15T01:02:32Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": true,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31051#issuecomment-3535239954\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7TCLkK\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"pgaudet\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"I dont think we can do that ? \",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-11-17T08:37:28Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31051#issuecomment-3540564234\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7TLTi0\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"raymond91125\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"Should we close this ticket then?\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-11-17T17:01:52Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31051#issuecomment-3542956212\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7TnkPR\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"cmungall\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"The conservative thing to do is add \\\"sensu metazoa\\\" to the label and add the TC (and remove the whackamole TCs that thereby become redundant). This is completely safe as the only annotations are in vertebrates (and mostly mammals). I think the direction we should go in is more specificity, not more vague fuzzy groupings, especially if we can't commit to populating.\\n\\nIt's tempting to go further. It's a pretty terrible grouping or target for direct annotation as @pgaudet says (the subclasses are fine). And it's very confusing to users as all of the obvious genes we'd expect to see are not present. But may not be worth the churn to make any major changes.\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-11-19T02:17:03Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31051#issuecomment-3550364625\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7Tpc9O\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"raymond91125\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"@cmungall  What do you mean by \\\"(and remove the whackamole TCs that thereby become redundant)\\\"? Remove the taxon constraints on GO:0032501 multicellular organismal process?\\nI thought we discourage using \\\"sensu\\\". Is that not the case?\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-11-19T05:22:00Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31051#issuecomment-3550859086\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7TqPyg\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"pgaudet\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"@raymond91125 \\n\\nWe have used similar phrases: (although, not exactly 'sensu') \\n[plant organ development](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0099402) versus [animal organ development](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0048513)\\n\\nSo we could change these terms to 'development of animal secondary sexual characteristics' (& male & female)\\n\\n@cmungall would that work ? \",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-11-19T06:50:48Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31051#issuecomment-3551067296\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws7TzgM_\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"cmungall\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"To me the advantage of the sensu nomenclature is that it clearly serves as a kind of editorial disambiguation note with zero ontological commitment. If we start saying things like \\\"animal secondary sexual characteristics\\\" it makes it sound like this is an actual grouping or even a homologous characteristic.\\n\\nIf we are going to keep the grouping IMO mammalian is more meaningful, we'd just have to get rid of these problematic annotations\\nhttps://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo/reference/PMID:34440752\\n\\n[whackamole](https://www.yourdictionary.com/whack-a-mole) -- I think of all of these hyper-specific TCs that have been made my individual MODs to prevent propagation in their species as like a game of whackamole, we need to keep adding more and more if GO is to be broadly useful outside MODs, when all we need to do is fix the problem at source.\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-11-19T16:00:50Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31051#issuecomment-3553493823\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws769f9p\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"raymond91125\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please review all the comments and make suggestions to a solution.\",\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
